England right-back Kieran Trippier has completed move to Spanish side Atletico Madrid from Tottenham. The 28-year-old, who joined Spurs from Burnley in June 2015 and played more than 100 times for the London club, has signed a four-year deal with the La Liga side. He had admitted he was not sure he would see out his Spurs contract, which was due to expire in 2022. Trippier is Atletico’s third major defensive signing of the summer. According to BBC, the transfer fee will be £20m.